HOW TO USE
THE EMERGENCY
OXYGEN MASK
1. WHERE TO LOCATE MASKS.
The oxygen masks are located in the center seat
back of three place seats, and in the aisle seat back
of the two place seats. In the forward and aft
lounge, masks are located overhead, or on
adjacent bulkheads.
These masks will be automatically released to you
whenever oxygen is required.
Jet flights are conducted above 25,000 ft. with the cabin pressurized
to an altitude of 5,000 to 8,000 ft. If the cabin pressure is lost,
you are at the same altitude as the aircraft, and it is imperative
that you immediately put on the oxygen mask as indicated below.
2. HOW TO USE. Take nearest mask firmly in
hand and pull it from its holder.
As mask iS
removed, a cord connecting it to the compartment
"must be pulled free." This allows oxygen to flow.
3. UNCOIL
OXYGEN
TUBE AND PLASTIC
BAG. The coiled oxygen tube, plastic bag, and
head band are stored inside the mask and should
be lifted out. The oxygen supply tube is long
enough that you may relax comfortably in your seat
after mask is on your face.
4. PLACE MASK OVER NOSE AND MOUTH.
Slip head band over head and adjust to fit. Do not
overtighten head band as this may misshape mask
and cause discomfort.
HOW TO
OPERATE
ESCAPE
SLIDE
1.
Open EXIT door-
2. Remove panel
Grasp slide bar and pull
down to floor
4. Hook bar into brackets
5. Pull inflation handle
down hard
6. Jump and sit in slide
PLEASE DO NOT REMOVE THIS CARD FROM AIRPLANE
